  "prompt": "Is posting links to your website allowed on Quora?",
  "response": "Yes, posting links to your website on Quora is generally allowed, but there are specific guidelines you need to follow. Quora encourages users to provide valuable and informative answers rather than simply promoting their own websites. Here are some important points to keep in mind:\n\n1. **Relevance**: Ensure that any links you share are relevant to the question being asked and add value to your answer.\n\n2. **Quality Answers**: Focus on providing a comprehensive and helpful answer. If your website offers additional information or resources that enhance your answer, including a link may be beneficial.\n\n3. **Avoid Spamming**: Refrain from excessively posting links to your website, as this can be viewed as spammy behavior. Quora\u2019s moderation team may flag or remove your content if it seems promotional rather than informative.\n\n4. **Profile Linking**: You can include links to your website in your Quora profile, which can help establish credibility and attract visitors from interested users.\n\n5. **Community Guidelines**: Always adhere to Quora's policies and guidelines, as violating them can lead to your content being removed or your account being restricted.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you can share links effectively while maintaining the integrity of your contributions on the platform.",
